## 4. FIREBASE CONFIGURATION

### Hosting
```json
{
  "hosting": {
    "public": "dist",
    "rewrites": [{ "source": "**", "destination": "/index.html" }]
  }
}
```

### Firestore Collections (Existing)
```
users/{uid}           → user profiles, roles, macro targets
clients/{clientId}    → legacy client data
weeks/{weekId}        → weekly check-in submissions
videos/{videoId}      → video library entries
workouts/{workoutId}  → coach-assigned workouts
messages/{messageId}  → coach ↔ client messages
posts/{postId}        → community feed posts
posts/{postId}/comments/{commentId} → post comments
settings/{docId}      → app configuration
```

### New Firestore Collection (ADD — do not modify existing rules)
```
userPrograms/{userId}
  Fields:
    userId: string
    programId: string           // e.g. 'prog13'
    programName: string
    goal: WorkoutGoal
    split: string
    difficulty: 'beginner' | 'intermediate' | 'advanced'
    startDate: string           // ISO date string
    currentCycle: number        // starts at 1
    completedDays: number[]     // [1, 2, 3, 4]
    rotation: ProgramDay[]      // full 10-day array from restDayEngine
    assignedByCoach: boolean    // true if coach assigned, false if self-selected
    createdAt: Timestamp
    updatedAt: Timestamp
```

### Firestore Rules to ADD (append to existing firestore.rules)
```javascript
// ─── userPrograms/{userId} ─────────────────────────
// • User reads/writes their own program
// • Coach can read/write any user's program (for assignment)
match /userPrograms/{userId} {
  allow read: if isSignedIn() && (isOwner(userId) || isCoach());
  allow write: if isSignedIn() && (isOwner(userId) || isCoach());
}
```

### localStorage Keys (used until Firestore migration)
```
activeProgram_{userId}    → JSON of UserActiveProgram object
```

