## 7. FEATURE: WORKOUT WIZARD + PROGRAM TRACKING

### Complete User Flow

```
FLOW A — New user / No active program:

Workouts page opens
    ↓
STEP 1: Goal Selection
  6 goal cards displayed in 2×3 grid
  Each card: emoji + goal name + short description (EN or AR)
  User taps one card → highlights → [NEXT] button activates
    ↓
STEP 2: Difficulty Selection
  3 level cards displayed vertically
  Beginner: "New to training / returning after break / machine-based"
  Intermediate: "1-2 years / comfortable with free weights"
  Advanced: "3+ years / percentage-based lifting / heavy compounds"
  User taps one → [NEXT]
    ↓
STEP 3: Split Selection
  Cards filtered by goal + difficulty
  Each card shows: split name + sessions count + avg duration + "best for" tag
  ★ RECOMMENDED badge on top match
  User taps one → [SEE PROGRAM]
    ↓
STEP 4: Program Preview
  Shows 10-day rotation (day names only, no exercise detail)
  Program name + description
  Two buttons: [ASSIGN THIS PROGRAM] and [← BACK]
    ↓
STEP 5: Confirmation screen
  "Your program is ready!"
  Shows: goal + split + difficulty + cycle info
  [START MY PROGRAM 🚀]
    ↓
Saved to localStorage + Firestore userPrograms collection
Redirect to Dashboard
ActiveProgramCard now visible on Dashboard

─────────────────────────────────────────────────

FLOW B — Has active program:

Workouts page opens
    ↓
Shows current program banner:
  Program name + goal + difficulty
  Day X/10 progress
  [DELETE & CHOOSE NEW PROGRAM] button (with confirmation dialog)
    ↓
Below: Browse mode (Netflix-style rows by goal)
  All 42 programs browsable (read-only, no assign button)

─────────────────────────────────────────────────

FLOW C — Workout Day View:

User taps [START TODAY'S WORKOUT] from dashboard
    ↓
WorkoutDayView opens:
  Header: day name + goal banner
  Goal banner: mode label + today's focus + rest guidance + weight guidance
  Exercise list: each exercise as a card
    ↓
Exercise card shows:
  Exercise name (tappable)
  Sets × reps
  Rest time with timer icon
  Notes badge (REST PAUSE, etc.) if present
  Rep scheme explanation (parsed from reps string)
    ↓
Tap exercise name → ExerciseModal slides up from bottom:
  GIF (full width, auto-loops)
  Muscle groups (primary + secondary)
  Instructions (in user's language from LanguageContext)
  Coach tips
  Common mistakes
  Language auto from LanguageContext — no manual toggle
    ↓
Bottom of workout:
  [✅ MARK DAY AS COMPLETE] button
    ↓
  For rest days: RestDayCard (education + acknowledgment button)
    ↓
Completion screen:
  Celebration animation
  "Day X complete!"
  Show tomorrow's session name
  [BACK TO DASHBOARD]
    ↓
After Day 10:
  "Cycle N complete! 🎉"
  cycle counter increments
  completedDays resets to []
  same program continues

─────────────────────────────────────────────────

FLOW D — Coach assigns program to coaching client:

Coach goes to client profile
Selects a program from the 42 programs
Clicks [ASSIGN TO CLIENT]
  → writes to Firestore userPrograms/{clientId}
  → assignedByCoach: true
  → overrides any self-selected program
Client's dashboard shows assigned program
Client CANNOT delete coach-assigned program
  (delete button hidden if assignedByCoach === true)
```

