### Science-Based Patterns Per Split

```
These are based on biochemistry + biomechanics research:

CNS Recovery:          24-72h after heavy compound work
Muscle Protein Synthesis: peaks 24-48h, resolves 48-72h
Cortisol normalization: 24-48h post heavy session
Connective tissue:     slowest recovery — 48-72h minimum
Glycogen resynthesis:  24-48h depending on depletion

POWERLIFTING (highest CNS demand):
  Pattern: 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT
  Rationale: @85-95% training requires full 48h CNS clearance
  Critical: Squat day and Deadlift day NEVER within 48h of each other
  Bench can follow Squat (different CNS pathway)
  OHP can follow Bench (low additional CNS demand)

  Cycle: Squat→REST→Bench→REST→Deadlift→REST→OHP→REST→Squat2→REST
  Then: Bench2→REST→Deadlift2→REST (continues in next cycle)

FULL BODY (high CNS, all groups):
  Pattern: 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT
  Rationale: Every session hits all muscle groups, need 48h between ANY two sessions
  Never two full body sessions consecutive — non-negotiable

  Cycle: FB-A→REST→FB-B→REST→FB-C→REST→FB-D→REST→FB-E→REST

PUSH/PULL/LEGS (moderate CNS):
  Pattern: 3 ON → 1 OUT → 3 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT
  Rationale:
    Push+Pull = antagonist pairing = safe consecutive
    Legs = high CNS (squats/deadlifts) = needs rest after
    Arms day = lowest CNS = placed strategically after Pull
  
  Cycle: Push1→Pull1→Legs1→REST→Push2→Pull2→Legs2→REST→Arms→REST

UPPER/LOWER (moderate CNS):
  Pattern: 2 ON → 1 OUT → 2 ON → 1 OUT → 2 ON → 1 OUT → rest fills remaining
  Rationale:
    Upper+Lower alternates non-competing groups = safe pairing
    Lower day always needs rest after (quad/hamstring CNS demand)
    Upper days lower CNS can be closer together
  
  Cycle: Upper1→Lower1→REST→Upper2→Lower2→REST→Upper3→Lower3→REST→REST

BRO SPLIT (moderate, isolated groups):
  Pattern: 2 ON → 1 OUT → 2 ON → 1 OUT → 3 ON → 1 OUT
  Rationale:
    Chest+Back = antagonists = safe pairing
    Legs always isolated with rest after
    Shoulders = lowest CNS of compound days
    Arms = lowest overall CNS = can follow anything
  
  Cycle: Chest→Back→REST→Legs→REST→Shoulders→Arms→Chest2→REST→BackTraps

HIIT/CIRCUIT (metabolic not mechanical):
  Pattern: 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → 1 OUT → 1 ON → rest fills
  Rationale:
    Metabolic stress > mechanical = cortisol stays elevated 24-36h
    Full body HIIT back-to-back = overtraining
    Shorter sessions but higher metabolic cost
  
  Cycle: Circuit-A→REST→Circuit-B→REST→Circuit-C→REST→Circuit-D→REST→Circuit-E→REST

CARDIO-FOCUSED (lowest CNS):
  Pattern: 3 ON → 1 OUT → 3 ON → 1 OUT (aggressive, cardio recovers faster)
  Rationale:
    Zone 2 cardio = minimal mechanical damage
    Can train 5-6x/week at low intensity
    Higher intensity sessions (HIIT cardio) need 48h
  
  Cycle: Session-A→Session-B→Session-C→REST→Session-D→Session-E→Session-F→REST→REST→REST

GOAL MODIFIER (applied after split pattern):
  fat_loss:    standard pattern (higher rep = faster recovery)
  muscle_gain: standard pattern
  strength:    add +1 rest day vs standard (heaviest loading)
  recomp:      standard pattern
  maintenance: can reduce rest by 1 (lower intensity)
  endurance:   can reduce rest by 1 (high rep = less mechanical damage)
```

